text:
ComeCare side - team report

Progress:
• Able to fetch form data from CommCare as a list.
• Able to replicate the OpenAPI specification with stubs for the endpoints.
Challenges:
• Doesn't seem possible to create forms using the CommCare REST API. We are not implementing the POST/PUT requests as a result.
• Filtering on fields seems to be a challenge using the CommCare REST API. This may mean we fetch a lot of data and perform filtering on that set.
• Unclear what the mapping should be from CommCare data to the JSI schema.

"I took a quick look at the API queries on the spreadsheet, and wanted to pass along some quick thoughts on the two API related questions I was hoping you could share with your team:
1. First, you _can_ create forms (which I assume you mean submit forms) via our <https://confluence.dimagi.com/display/commcarepublic/Submission+API|submission API>. 
2. Secondly, I see that filtering on fields seems to be a challenge. You _can_ filter on certain parameters when pulling from data. You can find the valid parameters at the top of this <https://confluence.dimagi.com/display/commcarepublic/List+Forms|page>."
